Known hypersensitivity to the active substance, or to any of the excipients [see 

                           Adverse Reactions (6)

                        ].

text.paragraph:
Lipid substudy: In the extended adjuvant setting (MA-17), based on a median duration of follow-up of 62 months, there was no significant difference between letrozole tablets and placebo in total cholesterol or in any lipid fraction over 5 years. Use of lipid lowering drugs or dietary management of elevated lipids was allowed. [see 
                                 Warnings and Precautions(5.2)
                              ] .
